                            <comment id="15473949" author="mreutegg" created="Thu, 8 Sep 2016 14:04:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added ignored test: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1759826&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1759826&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15473999" author="mreutegg" created="Thu, 8 Sep 2016 14:25:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A potential solution is to add a condition &lt;tt&gt;notEquals(REV_RECOVERY_LOCK, RecoverLockState.ACQUIRED.name())&lt;/tt&gt; to the UpdateOp.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15474048" author="reschke" created="Thu, 8 Sep 2016 14:44:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;...yes, but if the DS operation than fails we absolutely should re-read the report so that we can LOG useful diagnostics...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
